## 5. Features — Full Specification

### Feature 1: AI-Powered Personalized Onboarding

**What it does:** The user names their AI buddy, answers a 7-question financial profile quiz, and receives an AI-generated profile summary in plain language.

**Quiz questions and why each matters:**
1. *What's your main financial goal?* (emergency fund / investing / retirement / debt payoff) — routes the user to the most relevant dashboard widgets
2. *How would you describe your money knowledge?* (beginner / intermediate / advanced) — sets Claude's explanation complexity
3. *How often do you save each month?* (never / sometimes / always) — calibrates savings goal aggressiveness
4. *What types of investing interest you?* (stocks / ETFs / crypto / real estate) — populates watchlist defaults
5. *How do you react when an investment drops 20%?* (sell immediately / hold / buy more) — sets risk tolerance score (1–10)
6. *What's your investment time horizon?* (< 1 year / 1–5 years / 5+ years) — informs long-term vs. short-term guidance
7. *What's your approximate monthly income?* (optional) — enables spending-as-percent-of-income calculations

**Output:** Claude generates a 3–4 sentence financial profile like: *"You're a beginner investor with a moderate risk tolerance and a 5+ year horizon — perfect for learning to build a diversified ETF portfolio. Your main focus right now should be building a $5,000 emergency fund before investing. Finn will keep your explanations simple and always show both sides of every recommendation."*

**Success metric:** ≥ 85% of new users complete onboarding (industry benchmark for fintech onboarding completion: 60–70%).

