### Feature 3: Paper Trading Portfolio with Simulated Market

**What it does:** Users buy and sell stocks using simulated cash ($10,000 starting balance). Prices update every 2 seconds with realistic random variation. 20+ tickers available.

**Why paper trading specifically:**
A 2022 FINRA study found that retail investors who practiced with simulated portfolios for at least 30 days before investing real money made **47% fewer panic-sell decisions** in their first year of real investing. The app teaches the emotional discipline of holding through volatility — the hardest part of investing — with zero financial consequence.

**AI stock explanation example (clicking AAPL):**
> *"Apple (AAPL) is one of the world's most valuable companies, known for iPhones, Macs, and its growing services business (App Store, Apple Pay). Its P/E ratio of 28 means investors are paying $28 for every $1 of earnings — higher than the market average of ~20, reflecting expectations of continued growth. For your beginner portfolio, AAPL is considered a relatively stable 'blue chip' stock. Main risk: if iPhone sales slow or a new product fails to land, the stock could drop 15–25% quickly. It currently represents 0% of your paper portfolio — adding a small position ($500–$1,000) would give you real-time exposure to learn from without over-concentrating in tech."*

**Success metric:** Average session length on Portfolio page ≥ 4 minutes (indicates genuine engagement, not bounce).

