### Feature 12: Personalized AI Insight Cards

**What it does:** Every page surfaces 3 contextual insight cards from the user's named buddy. Cards include a category badge (BUDGET / PORTFOLIO / MARKET / RECOMMENDATION), risk label (low / medium / high), and accept/dismiss controls.

**Why the insight card pipeline is technically differentiated:**
Most AI-powered apps send a prompt and display the response. Finance Buddy's insight pipeline is a multi-stage extraction chain: (1) the server assembles the user's full financial snapshot — budget totals, portfolio holdings, risk profile, and open goals — into a single structured context block; (2) Claude is instructed to return a JSON array of cards with strict schema (type, title ≤60 chars, body, priority, risk); (3) the server validates every field against enum lists and bounds — malformed or out-of-schema cards are silently dropped and replaced with pre-written fallbacks; (4) only valid cards are stored and returned to the client. This structured extraction approach — prompt → parse → validate → fallback — is meaningfully harder to replicate than a raw "ask Claude a question" implementation because it requires a reliable schema contract between the LLM output and the application data layer.

**Insight card anatomy:**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [BUDGET]                         ⚠ MEDIUM   │
│ Dining expenses up 23%                      │
│                                             │
│ You spent $340 on dining vs. your $277      │
│ average. Cooking at home 3x/week saves      │
│ ~$100/month — enough to hit your emergency  │
│ fund goal 3 weeks sooner.                   │
│                                             │
│ [Got it]                    [Dismiss]       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

